text:
The movie "Zakhar Berkut" in the box office has already raised 32 million UAH

05 Nov 2019, 17:11


Zakhar Berkut, a Ukrainian historical film since its October 10 premiere, has raised UAH 32 million in cash in Ukraine.

This was reported on the official page of the film on Facebook.
“Over 400,000 viewers and over 32 million hryvnias. That is how much the historical action “Zakhar Berkut” has rented today, ”the message reads.
We will remind, earlier it was reported that the movie "Zakhar Berkut" collected more than 13 million UAH less than in a week of rent.

Certificate.

The film "Zakhar Berkut" is the largest Ukrainian cinema project since independence, made on the basis of Ivan Franko's story. Director - Akhtem Seitablaev, one of the most famous contemporary figures of Ukrainian cinema and theater, winner of many film awards, in particular, worked on films "Haytarma", "Alien Prayer", "Cyborg";
The lead role is Robert Patrick, who is remembered by viewers in Terminator-2;
Star actors from all over the world: Ukraine, USA, UK, Mongolia, Kazakhstan;
A huge international team of film professionals;
Shooting in incredible corners of the Carpathians;
Unique scale scenery that has no analogues in domestic cinema;
Hundreds of unique handmade costumes, weapons, utensils and belongings;
Stunning stunts and special effects.

